rationale: This trade maximizes Team A's projected points by consolidating depth for elite talent. Trading a top QB3 (Trevor Lawrence) and an elite TE (George Kittle) from positions of strength allows Team A to acquire an elite RB1 (Bijan Robinson) and a high-upside WR1 (Malik Nabers), significantly boosting the starting lineup's weekly scoring potential while retaining top-tier starters in Josh Allen and Mark Andrews.
